Class InstanceCreator.ManagedInstance

Enclosing class:
InstanceCreator
private class InstanceCreator.ManagedInstance
extends java.lang.Object

This structure aims to manage a configuration. It stores all necessary information to create an instance and to track the factory.

Method Detail

matchNameAndVersion

public boolean matchNameAndVersion(IPojoFactory factory)
Checks if the required factory name match with the given factory. This methods checks only the name, and not the configuration.

Parameters:
factory - the factory to test
Returns:
true if the factory name and the version (if set) match, false otherwise.

match

public boolean match(IPojoFactory factory)
Checks if the given factory match with the factory required by this instance. A factory matches if its name or its class name is equals to the 'component' property of the instance. Then the acceptability of the configuration is checked.

Parameters:
factory - the factory to confront against the current instance.
Returns:
true if the factory matches.

create

public void create(IPojoFactory factory)
Creates the instance by using the given factory.

Parameters:
factory - the factory to use to create the instance. The factory must match.

dispose

public void dispose()
Disposes the current instance if not null.
